{"questionId":"16452726","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A farmer is growing a field of wheat plants. The height, <em>H</em> cm, of each plant can be modelled by a normal distribution with mean &mu; and standard deviation &sigma;.</p>\n<p>It is known that P(<em>H</em> &lt; 94.6) = 0.288 and P(<em>H</em> &gt; 98.1) = 0.434.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The farmer measures 100 randomly selected plants. Any plant with a height greater than 98.1 cm is considered ready to harvest. Heights of plants are independent of each other.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the probability that exactly&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>34</mn></math>&nbsp;plants are ready to harvest.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>recognition of Binomial distribution&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>(M1)</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>X</mi><mo>~</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>100</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>434</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>34</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0133198</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0133</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[2 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"16452726","referenceCode":"23N.2.SL.TZ2.9ci","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the probability that exactly 34 plants are ready to harvest.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.8—Binomial distribution","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.11—Conditional and independent probabilities, test for independence"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}
